# Copy to .env.local to override. Both settings are optional.

# Where the browser sends API calls. Unset (the default) means same-origin:
# the SPA calls /api/*, which Vite proxies to the backend in development. This
# works from any machine — including a browser on another host via
# `pnpm dev --host` — because no backend host is baked into the bundle.
#
# Set this only if the API really is on a different origin. That is cross-origin,
# so the backend must also allow it: ORACLE_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://192.168.1.2:5173
# Note Vite inlines this at build time; a built bundle cannot be repointed later.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.2:8000

# Where the Vite dev proxy forwards /api. Resolved on the machine running Vite,
# so loopback is correct even when you browse from another machine.
# ORACLE_API_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:8000
